Sentencas: Nanocrystalline perovskite oxide based cathode materials Ln(0.6)Sr(0.4)Co(0.2)Fe(0.8)O(3-delta) (Ln = Nd, Sm, Gd) (LnSCF) has been synthesized by gel-combustion method using glycine as a fuel.
Titulo: Crystal structure, thermal expansion, electrical conductivity and chemical compatibility studies of nanocrystalline Ln0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ (Ln = Nd, Sm, Gd)

Sentencas: The decomposition and crystallization behavior or precursor was studied by TG/DTA analysis.
Titulo: Crystal structure, thermal expansion, electrical conductivity and chemical compatibility studies of nanocrystalline Ln0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ (Ln = Nd, Sm, Gd)

Sentencas: The detection and identification of impurities in the powders obtained after combustion was done by FTIR spectroscopy.
Titulo: Crystal structure, thermal expansion, electrical conductivity and chemical compatibility studies of nanocrystalline Ln0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ (Ln = Nd, Sm, Gd)

Sentencas: Crystal structure, thermal expansion, electrical conductivity of composition Ln(0.6)Sr(0.4)Co(0.2)Fe(0.8)O(3-delta) (Ln = Nd, Sm. Gd) were studied as a function of temperature.
Titulo: Crystal structure, thermal expansion, electrical conductivity and chemical compatibility studies of nanocrystalline Ln0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ (Ln = Nd, Sm, Gd)

Sentencas: X-Ray diffraction study shows that phase pure perovskite structure with orthorhombic symmetry is obtained after calcinations at 1173 K, except in the case of Gd0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (GdSCF) in which cubic phase is also present besides the orthorhombic phase.
Titulo: Crystal structure, thermal expansion, electrical conductivity and chemical compatibility studies of nanocrystalline Ln0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ (Ln = Nd, Sm, Gd)

Sentencas: The average crystallite sizes of samples were obtained by Scherrer's equation and were found to be between 1823 inn.
Titulo: Crystal structure, thermal expansion, electrical conductivity and chemical compatibility studies of nanocrystalline Ln0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ (Ln = Nd, Sm, Gd)

Sentencas: Linear thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) of these cathode materials was determined by dilatometry technique.
Titulo: Crystal structure, thermal expansion, electrical conductivity and chemical compatibility studies of nanocrystalline Ln0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ (Ln = Nd, Sm, Gd)

Sentencas: The composition Nd0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (NdSCF) shows the lowest TEC value.
Titulo: Crystal structure, thermal expansion, electrical conductivity and chemical compatibility studies of nanocrystalline Ln0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ (Ln = Nd, Sm, Gd)

Sentencas: The dependence of the electrical conductivity on temperature was measured from room temperature to 1173 K using four probe method.
Titulo: Crystal structure, thermal expansion, electrical conductivity and chemical compatibility studies of nanocrystalline Ln0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ (Ln = Nd, Sm, Gd)

Sentencas: Nd0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta shows the maximum electrical conductivity followed by Sm0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (SmSCF).
Titulo: Crystal structure, thermal expansion, electrical conductivity and chemical compatibility studies of nanocrystalline Ln0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ (Ln = Nd, Sm, Gd)

Sentencas: Morphological analysis of the powder calcined at higher temperatures was studied by scanning electron microscope (SEM).
Titulo: Crystal structure, thermal expansion, electrical conductivity and chemical compatibility studies of nanocrystalline Ln0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ (Ln = Nd, Sm, Gd)

Sentencas: The chemical compatibility of these cathode materials has been studied with the electrolyte material La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta (LSGM) prepared by gel-combustion method.
Titulo: Crystal structure, thermal expansion, electrical conductivity and chemical compatibility studies of nanocrystalline Ln0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ (Ln = Nd, Sm, Gd)
